<biogHist>
<abstract>In this oral history interview held by the National Library of Australia, John Padfield reflects on his work in the child protection system in Victoria. He discusses his time working at Allambie and Winlaton, attitudes towards children in care and their families, and the impact of permanent care on children.</abstract>
